HEADWORD: Semifable
<hw>Sem"i*fa`ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That which is
part fable and part truth; a mixture of truth and fable.</def>
<rj><au>De Quincey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

